specifically explain the basis for its statement it appears that the ref response assumed that the former dpm could have accessed his email and files on the ref network through his laptop see ar tab y ref responses ¶  the co stated that she believed that the former dpm would have had access through the ref computer networks to information pertaining to cacis incumbent contract and the alternative staffing procurement the co also stated that she was aware of two computer systems at the ref where information was stored the refs classified secret internet protocol router network siprnet and a networked drive known as the k drive to which all government and contractor personnel had access tr at   in this regard the co stated that she believed that all government and personnel had access to the k drive for this reason she believed that the ref would have used only the siprnet to store procurement sensitive information tr at   the co also acknowledged that she did not access the siprnet and believed that there were no files to access on the k drive tr at   in her testimony the co states that her understanding of the way in which the ref maintained the alternative staffing procurement files was based on conversations with the ref contracting team lead tr at  she acknowledged however that she did not ask him whether the former dpm had access to those files tr at  the co also acknowledges that she did not investigate whether the former dpm had actually accessed any ref computer files during his terminal leave tr at  the former dpm acknowledged that he had access to both the k drive and the ref siprnet when he had his computer ar tab x decl of former dpm august   ¶  tr at  the former dpm further states that he was not aware of any folders on the k drive that contained procurement sensitive information relating to the alternate staffing procurement tr at  the former dpm stated that he believed that all government and contractor personnel could access the k drive and that it 